line_1: Thou'se get the saul o' boot.
line_2: The swap we yet will do't;

line_1: Then he's your brother too to boot.
line_2: His worth no mortal dares dispute:

line_1: With skill a Shoe to patch, to stitch a Boot!
line_2: His sole ambition and his prime pursuit,

line_1: Besides, I'm veh'mently in love to boot,
line_2: Thus Fate conspires, and what can I do to 't?

line_1: While Hebe, Minerva, and twenty to boot,
line_2: With gifts all celestial have trick'd me her out.

line_1: Smit with the love of the laconic boot,
line_2: The cap and wig succinct, the silken suit,

line_1: That I wou'd, quoth the Father, and thank you to boot;
line_2: But our Actions, You know, with our Duty must suit.
